ith industry experts and analysis of thirdparty data its aim is to provide a guide to today’s market offer a glimpse of what the gulf’s luxury sector might look like at the end of this current transition and offer hints on how to cope with the changing luxury ecosystem   the white paper is available in english french and italian    download white paper  the chalhoub group third white paper “luxury in the gulf a sustainable future” sets out to explore the gulf region beyond the luxury sector drawing on lessons learnt from the inherent link between basic luxury principles and promoting sustainability in the middle east the white paper is available in english french and italian  download white paper  the chalhoub group second white paper “gulf luxury consumers a world apart” aims to unveil the particular lifestyle and the specific codes associated with luxury consumption in the gulf it defines a set of three consumer archetypes together with the key trends and potential evolution of luxury demand in the region the white paper is available in english french and italian  download white paper  the chalhoub group “luxury in the middle east an easy sell” is the group’s first white paper examining the environment for luxury in the region the size and structure of the market and its consumers’ approach to luxury specifically the nuances between them within the regionthe white paper is available in english french and italian  download press releases a new luxury norm – chalhoub group launches white paper to explore the evolving face of luxury in the gulf london  may  chalhoub group the leading partner for luxury across… read more  the chalhoub group’s new venture in the fb world chalhoub group the leading partner for luxury across the middle east is pleased… read more  chalhoub group announces its newest concept store level kids chalhoub group the leading partner for luxury across the middle east is pleased… read more  tryano chalhoub group’s latest specialty store chalhoub gr