he middle east is evolving as it reaches a maturity phase and introduce the concept of a new norm – a new way of doing business to adapt to this changing luxury ecosystem   the new norm for luxury in the gulf looks beyond those geopolitical and economic challenges facing the region such as a prolonged period of low oil prices and exchange rate fluctuations and goes deeper to understand the profound forces that are occurring within the gulf luxury sector itself – to reveal a more mature face characterized by huge untapped potential   the group’s research in the middle east has found that   the number of highnetworth individuals in the region and their wealth is actually increasing with numbers set to grow by  compared to  growth in europe and north america by  while a growing middle class and number of women in the workplace also represent an increasing pool of consumers with promising purchasing power the business environment is more formally defined and framed by regulation addressing governance labour laws and consumer protection the region has one of the highest rates of luxury brand penetration in the world the region is displaying a maturing retail environment in terms of expanding available retail space and the variety of shopping environments the emergence of digital in the luxury retail sector in the gulf means that traditional marketing and the conventional instore retail experience are being upended luxury consumers are evolving and now seek more experientialfocused consumption comparing prices service quality and availability of the latest products   with this maturing phase underway the role of local partner’s such as chalhoub group has become even more pronounced in terms of their ability to draw on their extensive experience in the gulf to support international brands with their development against a changing luxury backdrop   the group’s white paper identifies key attributes of today’s local partner in order to help brands adapt and thrive in the middle east under the new norm   shares risks fosters operational efficiency through economies of scale and “plug and play” shared services applies its networks and knowledge of the region to help address the increased complexity of regulations and decisionmaking – for example in order to ensure a smooth registration process chalhoub group operates special compliance teams to prepare the required  documentation and then followup with local authorities to ensure fast approval leverages its extensive customer experience to impart customercentric bespoke product offers and services – for example chalhoub group’s guest experience initiative designed to take the luxury shopping experience to the next level nurtures innovation to create marketrelevant and compelling shopping experiences – for example chalhoub group’s unique concept store level shoes in dubai mall which delivers a revolutionary immersive shoe experience across sqm   patrick chalhoub coceo chalhoub group commented the gulf region has witnessed a period of abundance for the past  years with the building of incredible infrastructure and the development of the education of its young and vibrant population   it is now entering a new phase of maturity of knowledge of seriousness and of stronger governance despite the immediate geopolitical and economic challenges this is a region of wealth and of steady growth to be successful we will have to be aspirational meaningful and competitive and adapt to the changes and to the new norm”     ends  about chalhoub group the chalhoub group is the leading partner for luxury across the middle east since  as an expert in retail distribution and marketing services based in dubai the group has become a major player in the beauty fashion and gift sectors regionally by blending its middle east expertise and intimate knowledge of luxury the chalhoub group is building brands in the region by offering service excellence to all its partners and a unique experience to its customers with a